{
  "stem": "1316.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "When we came back, we had the also traditional meal.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But then it was the-- the Sabbath was disturbed because guests became-- began to arrive to the-- to the yard, to the back door, to have snacks, to have drinks, especially in the summer, in that season.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And the father couldn't-- it was painful, but he couldn't refuse because the other restaurant-- restaurateurs in the-- in the area also let in people on Shabbos.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And he had a dilemma how to let in people.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "My sister took the money.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "So the Shabbos was partly disturbed, although he was-- he didn't like it, but he couldn't help it.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "On holidays, I remember Hanukkah, at the cheder-- when I still was at the cheder.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And it was in-- in the court of the Otwock [POLISH] was a big court.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And they used to gather all the children from the cheders from the Talmud, Torah, in the-- in the synagogue of the Otwock [POLISH].",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And we stood on the tables, all on the tables, on the benches, viewing the shamash, the beadle go and light the candles.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And this was interesting.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "I don't know if in other places was this custom.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "We used to yell together, 'He goes, he goes,' as he moves, 'He lights, he lights, he lights.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "He hangs, he hangs.' It was very [LAUGHS] joyful for the children.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And then we hurried home for the Hanukkah, for plays for the dreidel, for the latkes, and so on, and this was Hanukkah.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Purim was very memorable because I attended the-- the Bikur holim society.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "We children went to see how they dress up-- my father was dressing up-- how they formed the parties.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "We followed them on the streets.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "They used to come in the houses and stores and dance, entertain.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
